exports[`characterize: solo cartoon + wardrobe-only brand 1`] = `
"Transform this photo into a 3D animated character portrait in the style of Pixar and Disney Animation Studios (The Incredibles, Coco, Up, Brave). Do not add anyone not in the original photo.\\n\\nPreserve accurately: skin tone, eye color, hair color, hairstyle, facial hair, glasses, jewelry, clothing, and any visible accessories or distinguishing features. The portrait must be immediately recognizable as the same person.\\n\\nStyle: High-quality Pixar-style 3D render with warm, rich color grading. Big round expressive eyes with detailed iris reflections, soft rounded features with a touch of stylization. Smooth subsurface scattering on skin for that signature Pixar porcelain glow. Rich fabric and hair textures with individual strand detail. Every surface should have the polished, tactile quality of a Pixar film frame.\\n\\nBody proportions: Keep the body realistically proportioned — normal adult height, limbs, and torso like The Incredibles characters. Do NOT make the body short, stocky, or compressed. The face and head can be slightly stylized but the body should look natural and well-proportioned.\\n\\nLighting: Warm cinematic Pixar-style lighting — soft key light with golden tones, gentle fill light, and a subtle cool rim light. Soft ambient occlusion in creases and under the chin.\\n\\nComposition: Frame from the waist up. Give them a warm, friendly expression.\\nThis photo has exactly 1 person. The output must contain exactly 1 human figure — do not add, invent, or hallucinate any additional people. Anything else in the photo (objects, posters, screens, reflections) is NOT a person.\\nClothing: Dress the subject in this exact outfit: A black hockey jersey with silver LA Kings crest on the chest.\\n\\nThe input images named brand_ref_0.png show the outfit visually.\\nPreserve accurately: skin tone, eye color, hair color and style, facial hair, glasses, facial structure.\\nLogos and text: Copy the exact logos, crests, numbers, and text from the reference images. Do NOT invent, add, or modify any text or symbols.\\nWear an LA Kings hockey jersey.\\nREMINDER: The art style described above takes ABSOLUTE priority. The brand/clothing references are ONLY for the outfit — do NOT let them influence the rendering style, line work, colors, or visual aesthetic.\\nBackground: Recreate the background from the original photo in the same art style. Keep it natural and consistent with the scene.\\n\\nFINAL STYLE LOCK: Render the entire output in this exact art style: Pixar-style 3D animated portrait with warm colors and rich textures. The clothing and background descriptions above describe subject matter, not rendering technique — they must not override the chosen art style.\\n\\nFINAL REMINDER: Exactly 1 human in the output. No other people. Anything else visible (objects, posters, screens, reflections, background figures) must NOT become a person."
`;

